pane Filling","content":["1 lemon, thin peelings of skin only","120 g caster sugar","120 g butter, soft","2 medium eggs","120 g ground almonds","15 g plain flour"]},{"title":"Glaze","content":["1 Tbsp apricot jam, melted"]}],"id":"r130424","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-zVjBadW3Qq8\/XZWdX_Vi2VI\/AAAAAAAAeks\/-5ia7LpsW-gW_Ump9G26kUEGKdvwJrKUwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Ffp3drB7E0ZEh-g5.png","title":"Pear Frangipane","publishedAt":"2016-10-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.7 g","fat":"28.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"36.8 g","calories":"1800 kJ \/ 430 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, tart tin (Ø 22 cm), rolling pin, pastry brush, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Grind your own almonds if desired. Place 120 g blanched almonds in mixing bowl before beginning recipe then grind <strong>10 sec\/speed 10<\/strong>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside until needed.","The pears will be just cooked (a knife should just pierce them easily) – they will continue to cook in the oven.","To prepare the pears, cut them in half lengthways and, using a teaspoon, scoop out and discard the core from the centre.","Scatter 1 Tbsp toasted flaked almonds over the surface for garnish, if desired.","Tinned pear halves can also be used. Omit step 2 and continue with recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","1h 30m","8 portions"]}